1
00:00:30,305 --> 00:00:32,904
While we're at school,
we should keep our distance.

2
00:00:32,905 --> 00:00:36,384
Sometimes we must push through
and do things we don't enjoy.

3
00:00:36,385 --> 00:00:38,824
If we see the benefit in it,

4
00:00:38,825 --> 00:00:41,305
we just carry on
and do what we must.

5
00:00:41,325 --> 00:00:44,385
"Saeng Karun Foundation."

6
00:00:55,135 --> 00:00:56,585
I wanted to apologize for...

7
00:00:56,605 --> 00:01:00,375
not being able to take care
of Saeng Karun well enough.

8
00:01:00,785 --> 00:01:02,235
Don't blame yourself.

9
00:01:02,795 --> 00:01:04,865
Everything has its causes.

10
00:01:34,305 --> 00:01:35,305
Dad.

11
00:01:36,175 --> 00:01:39,025
When you're done,
put it away in the cabinet.

12
00:01:39,385 --> 00:01:41,025
I hooked up a buzzer for you.

13
00:01:41,905 --> 00:01:44,225
No need to blow your lungs out.

14
00:01:44,945 --> 00:01:46,225
I am used to it.

15
00:01:48,635 --> 00:01:53,605
Fine. But if you keel over,
don't complain to me.

16
00:01:55,985 --> 00:01:56,985
Gotta work.

17
00:02:08,495 --> 00:02:09,495
Hey.

18
00:03:24,525 --> 00:03:27,385
Hello, yes. This is Somsak.

19
00:03:27,985 --> 00:03:30,185
I'd like to ask about my loan.

20
00:03:30,465 --> 00:03:31,665
Of course, sir.

21
00:03:31,865 --> 00:03:33,745
I was actually just
about to call you.

22
00:03:34,985 --> 00:03:38,905
If I can't make a payment,
what can the bank do for me?

23
00:03:39,385 --> 00:03:41,825
We're happy to
discuss your options, sir.

24
00:03:42,505 --> 00:03:44,265
But may I ask you something first?

25
00:03:44,825 --> 00:03:47,335
You mentioned before that
a sum of money was coming in.

26
00:03:47,855 --> 00:03:48,945
Has something come up?

27
00:03:49,905 --> 00:03:52,825
Just tell me straight.
What do I need to do?

28
00:03:53,645 --> 00:03:55,005
Right now, I have no money.

29
00:04:08,465 --> 00:04:11,745
Grandpa, I've got
some juicy gossip for you.

30
00:04:12,725 --> 00:04:13,725
Hmm?

31
00:04:14,545 --> 00:04:17,695
Guy said he'd keep trying to
win me over, right?

32
00:04:19,365 --> 00:04:19,905
Mm-hmm.

33
00:04:19,906 --> 00:04:21,465
He does flirt with me every day.

34
00:04:22,005 --> 00:04:25,325
He's like...
pulls something new every day.

35
00:04:25,345 --> 00:04:26,665
Never the same move twice.

36
00:04:28,495 --> 00:04:29,495
Grandpa.

37
00:04:30,745 --> 00:04:31,865
Not taking notes?

38
00:04:34,585 --> 00:04:36,025
I'm done writing BL novels.

39
00:04:38,785 --> 00:04:39,785
What do you mean?

40
00:04:41,065 --> 00:04:44,425
Are you going deaf?
I said I'm done.

41
00:04:44,675 --> 00:04:47,105
How can you just
drop it like that?

42
00:04:48,025 --> 00:04:49,605
It's a waste of time.

43
00:04:50,365 --> 00:04:53,825
Your time?
I've wasted more than just time.

44
00:04:55,185 --> 00:04:57,585
I went all out and dated a guy.

45
00:04:58,025 --> 00:04:59,825
Guy is my best friend.

46
00:05:00,785 --> 00:05:03,455
I was willing to lose a friend
so you could write a novel.

47
00:05:04,145 --> 00:05:07,065
Well, now you don't
have to force yourself.

48
00:05:07,205 --> 00:05:11,025
But didn't we do all this
to save the house?

49
00:05:12,145 --> 00:05:13,745
Don't give up now, Grandpa.

50
00:05:14,545 --> 00:05:15,665
It's not that.

51
00:05:16,985 --> 00:05:18,905
I've talked to the bank.

52
00:05:19,265 --> 00:05:23,225
They cut the payments
and extend the term of the loan.

53
00:05:24,065 --> 00:05:28,104
Extend? So what?
We still have no money to pay them.

54
00:05:28,105 --> 00:05:30,425
It's why I'm thinking
of a new way.

55
00:05:30,785 --> 00:05:32,864
Save, what's going on here?

56
00:05:32,865 --> 00:05:35,304
We heard it all the way
from the kitchen.

57
00:05:35,305 --> 00:05:37,904
Dad, he's gonna stop
writing the novel.

58
00:05:37,905 --> 00:05:39,745
- Aw?
- Sounds good to me.

59
00:05:40,305 --> 00:05:43,065
Sound good?
It could bring in a lot of money.

60
00:05:44,505 --> 00:05:47,865
Hey, the novel could be a flop.

61
00:05:51,365 --> 00:05:52,385
How could you know?

62
00:05:53,875 --> 00:05:55,305
You haven't finished it.

63
00:05:56,065 --> 00:05:57,385
It's not even published yet.

64
00:06:01,215 --> 00:06:03,025
Save, please stop.

65
00:06:03,785 --> 00:06:07,585
I wanna help too, okay?
I know we must do something...

66
00:06:08,955 --> 00:06:10,835
or we'll lose the house, right?

67
00:06:15,145 --> 00:06:16,145
Grandpa.

68
00:06:16,945 --> 00:06:18,625
You promised Khun Tiad, right?

69
00:06:19,505 --> 00:06:20,945
Aren't you ashamed to break it?

70
00:06:21,585 --> 00:06:24,435
I told you, I'm done.
Forget about it.

71
00:06:24,665 --> 00:06:26,345
Stop nagging me, will you?

72
00:06:28,855 --> 00:06:30,625
I get that it's hard.

73
00:06:32,235 --> 00:06:33,945
But I believed

74
00:06:34,865 --> 00:06:36,105
that you could do it.

75
00:06:37,665 --> 00:06:41,425
If you don't believe in yourself,
I have nothing more to say.

76
00:06:43,305 --> 00:06:44,305
Save.

77
00:06:44,675 --> 00:06:47,425
Watch your tone.
Apologize to him right now.

78
00:06:47,505 --> 00:06:48,505
Forget him.

79
00:06:49,945 --> 00:06:52,985
I know kids these days.
They don't care. Young or old.

80
00:06:56,355 --> 00:06:57,665
It's okay, Father.

81
00:06:57,985 --> 00:06:59,885
If you don't want to write,
it's okay.

82
00:06:59,945 --> 00:07:02,905
Our snack business is doing well,
both the shop and online.

83
00:07:03,025 --> 00:07:07,545
Little by little, we can certainly
put that toward the bank payments.

84
00:08:11,185 --> 00:08:14,825
I'm sorry, Grandfather. I failed.

85
00:08:16,215 --> 00:08:20,115
But I'll find another way
to come up with the money.

86
00:08:47,365 --> 00:08:48,505
Ahem.

87
00:08:57,215 --> 00:08:58,755
Oh, come on.

88
00:08:58,965 --> 00:09:02,505
Four of us here,
and only Save got the drink?

89
00:09:02,825 --> 00:09:04,785
What's that about?

90
00:09:05,535 --> 00:09:07,944
Never heard of a BL term?

91
00:09:07,945 --> 00:09:10,465
Aw... how sweet.

92
00:09:11,585 --> 00:09:15,025
- Just look at them.
- I'm melting.

93
00:09:15,125 --> 00:09:16,544
Will you cut it out?

94
00:09:16,545 --> 00:09:19,664
Come on, you're flustered.
You don't have to act mad.

95
00:09:19,665 --> 00:09:21,385
Aw... come on, smile.

96
00:09:21,855 --> 00:09:23,224
- Hey, hey.
- Hey.

97
00:09:23,225 --> 00:09:24,225
Stop right there.

98
00:09:29,835 --> 00:09:33,065
I didn't know you guys were here.
Take mine.

99
00:09:33,225 --> 00:09:35,205
- Sure, sure.
- Thanks, buddy.

100
00:09:35,705 --> 00:09:36,785
Thanks for sharing.

101
00:09:39,675 --> 00:09:41,305
That's more like it.

102
00:09:41,585 --> 00:09:42,705
Get back to studying.

103
00:09:48,595 --> 00:09:51,665
So annoying those guys.
Enough with the teasing already.

104
00:09:52,345 --> 00:09:53,665
Just let them be.

105
00:09:54,065 --> 00:09:56,975
Did something happen?
You seem wound up today.

106
00:09:57,595 --> 00:09:59,905
Ugh, it's just so hot out.

107
00:10:07,385 --> 00:10:09,985
Hey, don't be silly. Put that away.

108
00:10:10,705 --> 00:10:11,865
I just feel like it.

109
00:10:12,395 --> 00:10:14,225
Someone could see you. Put it away.

110
00:10:14,985 --> 00:10:16,425
Nobody's around.

111
00:10:18,425 --> 00:10:19,425
Guy.

112
00:10:22,905 --> 00:10:27,545
You said I could go all out
with you when we're alone.

113
00:10:37,535 --> 00:10:38,665
Huh.

114
00:10:43,445 --> 00:10:45,825
Wow, that's pricey.

115
00:10:46,265 --> 00:10:47,265
What?

116
00:10:47,945 --> 00:10:49,385
That art toy I've been wanting.

117
00:10:49,985 --> 00:10:52,585
Pakka by PYT Room.
Way out of my orbit.

118
00:10:53,495 --> 00:10:54,505
Huh.

119
00:11:08,625 --> 00:11:09,625
Mm-hmm.

120
00:11:10,425 --> 00:11:13,905
What kind of work is out there
for a 75-year-old?

121
00:11:17,105 --> 00:11:21,825
"There's actually quite a bit
a 75-year-old can still do."

122
00:11:22,235 --> 00:11:26,865
"Light work from home,
like handcrafts, cooking,"

123
00:11:26,945 --> 00:11:29,545
"or even selling plants."

124
00:11:33,585 --> 00:11:36,305
Anything that pays well?

125
00:11:38,145 --> 00:11:42,185
"That could be hard to come by."

126
00:11:42,275 --> 00:11:44,664
"But it's not
out of the question either."

127
00:11:44,665 --> 00:11:46,865
"Work that draws on
past experience, for instance."

128
00:11:47,015 --> 00:11:50,544
"Former teachers,
professors, lawyers,"

129
00:11:50,545 --> 00:11:52,624
"doctors, engineers."

130
00:11:52,625 --> 00:11:55,304
"Any of those can
launch an online course."

131
00:11:55,305 --> 00:11:59,865
"Income could range from
10,000 to 100,000 baht a month."

132
00:12:02,425 --> 00:12:03,625
Hmm.

133
00:12:10,185 --> 00:12:12,455
I was never in any of those fields.

134
00:12:14,765 --> 00:12:18,745
"Then what did you do?
Anything you're good at?"

135
00:12:23,515 --> 00:12:24,715
Hmm.

136
00:13:20,365 --> 00:13:23,825
Actually, it's better that
he's quitting the BL novel.

137
00:13:24,665 --> 00:13:25,825
I think so too.

138
00:13:26,355 --> 00:13:29,864
How could he keep up
with the young ones, really?

139
00:13:29,865 --> 00:13:31,685
- Right?
- Mm-hmm.

140
00:13:31,705 --> 00:13:36,425
At his age, he doesn't need to work.
Just sit around, and that's it.

141
00:13:36,945 --> 00:13:40,384
Right. He can barely even walk now.

142
00:13:40,385 --> 00:13:41,385
- Really?
- Yeah.

143
00:13:41,895 --> 00:13:46,105
And lately, I've noticed
he keeps dropping things too.

144
00:13:46,885 --> 00:13:49,025
Oh, I hadn't caught that.

145
00:14:43,665 --> 00:14:46,025
This is it when we get old,
huh, Mom?

146
00:14:52,795 --> 00:14:53,795
Before long,

147
00:14:55,465 --> 00:14:58,665
I'll be sitting still like a statue
just like you.

148
00:15:15,695 --> 00:15:16,825
Good afternoon, Grandfather.

149
00:15:17,125 --> 00:15:18,605
Oh, hello.

150
00:15:23,995 --> 00:15:25,785
Great-grandma, how are you?

151
00:15:26,895 --> 00:15:28,255
Good afternoon, Great-grandmother.

152
00:15:32,355 --> 00:15:34,865
Aw... being nicer to him, huh?

153
00:15:35,905 --> 00:15:37,345
Serves you right.

154
00:15:41,185 --> 00:15:42,185
Let's go live.

155
00:15:58,585 --> 00:16:01,345
Alright, everyone,
today's special promotion is

156
00:16:01,695 --> 00:16:03,705
buy five, get one free.

157
00:16:03,785 --> 00:16:05,945
Limited stock.
Once it's gone, it's gone.

158
00:16:06,225 --> 00:16:07,825
Get your orders in now.

159
00:16:13,295 --> 00:16:15,625
Phi Save isn't smiling today.

160
00:16:25,105 --> 00:16:26,705
Are you two fighting?

161
00:16:28,305 --> 00:16:29,225
Are you mad at me?

162
00:16:29,245 --> 00:16:30,245
No.

163
00:16:33,095 --> 00:16:35,745
Everyone, get the sales going.

164
00:16:36,025 --> 00:16:38,625
Don't wait. Don't hesitate.
Hit that button fast.

165
00:16:39,425 --> 00:16:40,504
New deal, everyone.

166
00:16:40,505 --> 00:16:43,745
If we hit 10,000 hearts, I'll plant
a kiss on Save's cheek live.

167
00:16:44,565 --> 00:16:45,565
Whatchu doing?

168
00:16:48,625 --> 00:16:49,825
Let's hit it, everyone.

169
00:16:50,905 --> 00:16:51,905
I'm not playing along.

170
00:16:52,755 --> 00:16:53,905
Why not?

171
00:16:56,665 --> 00:16:57,945
9,000 hearts, everyone.

172
00:16:59,995 --> 00:17:02,025
9,900...

173
00:17:03,505 --> 00:17:04,745
10,000 hearts.

174
00:17:07,265 --> 00:17:08,265
Hey, Guy.

175
00:17:10,065 --> 00:17:11,065
What were you thinking?

176
00:17:16,935 --> 00:17:18,055
Nothing to see here.

177
00:17:19,315 --> 00:17:20,585
He just went to the restroom.

178
00:17:22,065 --> 00:17:23,065
Hey.

179
00:17:25,365 --> 00:17:27,595
"Use of restricted terms detected"
What's going on?

180
00:17:40,505 --> 00:17:41,625
What's with you, Save?

181
00:17:41,945 --> 00:17:42,985
No, what's with you?

182
00:17:44,825 --> 00:17:47,305
I was just doing it for fun.
Numbers were flatlining.

183
00:17:47,945 --> 00:17:49,265
I wasn't actually going to do it.

184
00:17:49,825 --> 00:17:50,985
It wasn't fun for me.

185
00:17:51,885 --> 00:17:54,195
Save, what is actually
wrong with you?

186
00:17:54,215 --> 00:17:56,215
Are you mad at someone
and taking it out on me?

187
00:17:59,065 --> 00:18:02,065
Or wait, are you fighting
with your grandfather?

188
00:18:02,345 --> 00:18:04,305
I saw something's off
between you two.

189
00:18:10,095 --> 00:18:13,105
You can go now.
We've come as far as we can.

190
00:18:13,905 --> 00:18:15,105
Get out.

191
00:18:17,145 --> 00:18:18,185
I said get out.

192
00:18:18,905 --> 00:18:19,905
Out.

193
00:18:34,125 --> 00:18:35,125
Ugh.

194
00:19:26,165 --> 00:19:27,255
"Pakka, 4,500 baht."

195
00:19:27,305 --> 00:19:29,345
Wow, that's steep.

196
00:19:34,125 --> 00:19:35,825
"Account Balance: 5,523.00."

197
00:19:42,085 --> 00:19:44,985
One Pakka, please.
Can I get it today?

198
00:20:10,645 --> 00:20:12,625
Save.

199
00:20:14,075 --> 00:20:17,785
Guy said the channel got banned
because you dropped a swear word.

200
00:20:18,135 --> 00:20:21,585
The cart got wiped out.
We can't do live streams anymore.

201
00:20:22,865 --> 00:20:23,945
Sorry, Mom.

202
00:20:25,345 --> 00:20:28,315
I will... get the channel back.

203
00:20:31,005 --> 00:20:33,345
What were you two
even fighting about?

204
00:20:34,665 --> 00:20:37,465
Can't you talk it out?
He's been nothing but helpful.

205
00:20:37,745 --> 00:20:38,745
Huh.

206
00:20:39,515 --> 00:20:41,945
Well... we don't
need his help anymore.

207
00:20:43,265 --> 00:20:44,665
Grandpa's quit the novel anyway.

208
00:20:46,085 --> 00:20:47,605
No point in me
keeping going with him.

209
00:20:50,905 --> 00:20:51,985
Save.

210
00:22:07,465 --> 00:22:08,545
Go that way.

211
00:22:15,475 --> 00:22:17,105
Grandpa, Grandpa.

212
00:22:17,745 --> 00:22:19,825
The clip of you and Phi Save
went viral.

213
00:22:20,145 --> 00:22:21,145
What clip?

214
00:22:37,745 --> 00:22:40,145
"We're gonna hear from a grandpa
and his grandson."

215
00:22:46,505 --> 00:22:48,184
One at a time.

216
00:22:48,185 --> 00:22:51,785
The catch is
you can't hear each other.

217
00:22:52,435 --> 00:22:53,435
Okay.

218
00:22:53,455 --> 00:22:55,265
The headphones go on you first.

219
00:22:58,375 --> 00:22:59,375
Oh, sure.

220
00:23:05,185 --> 00:23:06,185
Okay?

221
00:23:09,145 --> 00:23:10,665
"Tell us about your grandson."

222
00:23:11,505 --> 00:23:12,715
"He's a sharp kid."

223
00:23:13,395 --> 00:23:15,875
"Bright, quick-witted."

224
00:23:16,945 --> 00:23:18,745
"Most of it he got
from me, of course."

225
00:23:20,525 --> 00:23:22,665
"He can be a handful sometimes."

226
00:23:23,465 --> 00:23:26,265
"But he's never said
a bad word about me."

227
00:23:28,025 --> 00:23:31,105
"What do you admire most about him?"

228
00:23:31,415 --> 00:23:32,905
"Quite a lot, really."

229
00:23:33,455 --> 00:23:36,705
"On the surface,
he doesn't care about much."

230
00:23:37,025 --> 00:23:39,025
"But deep down he's genuinely kind."

231
00:23:39,685 --> 00:23:42,385
"Generous, family-first."

232
00:23:42,865 --> 00:23:44,945
"He's always looked out for me."

233
00:23:56,235 --> 00:23:57,865
"Now tell us
about your grandfather."

234
00:23:58,005 --> 00:24:00,265
"The most stubborn man
in the house."

235
00:24:00,465 --> 00:24:03,025
Hey, be nice.

236
00:24:03,475 --> 00:24:06,345
"He puts on a tough front.
But that's all it is, a front."

237
00:24:06,985 --> 00:24:09,105
No one looks out for his family
like he does.

238
00:24:09,785 --> 00:24:12,185
"What do you admire most about him?"

239
00:24:12,505 --> 00:24:13,665
"He is brilliant."

240
00:24:14,565 --> 00:24:16,025
"My idol."

241
00:24:25,505 --> 00:24:27,405
- Huh.
- Hmm?

242
00:24:30,025 --> 00:24:32,425
No live streams for a week now.

243
00:24:32,565 --> 00:24:35,365
Don't know if we can
get the channel back.

244
00:24:36,395 --> 00:24:38,985
Save says we're waiting on
their email.

245
00:24:39,745 --> 00:24:41,345
Don't worry, Mart.

246
00:24:42,425 --> 00:24:44,345
We're still doing good
on consignment, right?

247
00:24:45,145 --> 00:24:46,825
Well enough, I suppose.

248
00:24:47,585 --> 00:24:49,425
We'll get the channel back.

249
00:24:50,385 --> 00:24:51,385
Hmm.

250
00:24:56,385 --> 00:24:58,945
Phi Sorn, why did you come back?

251
00:24:59,435 --> 00:25:02,105
Wait, why did you get these back?

252
00:25:03,345 --> 00:25:06,185
The shop returned them.
Said it's not moving.

253
00:25:06,385 --> 00:25:07,385
- What?
- Hey?

254
00:25:08,195 --> 00:25:09,984
How is that possible?

255
00:25:09,985 --> 00:25:12,185
It was going well last week.

256
00:25:19,895 --> 00:25:21,865
Hello, I'm here to restock.

257
00:25:22,345 --> 00:25:24,665
I'm sorry, we can't
take more right now.

258
00:25:24,695 --> 00:25:26,865
We still have quite a lot left.

259
00:25:28,985 --> 00:25:29,985
Really?

260
00:25:33,445 --> 00:25:34,445
See for yourself.

261
00:25:34,795 --> 00:25:37,825
Ha? How's this possible?

262
00:25:38,225 --> 00:25:39,945
Last week, they were sold out.

263
00:25:40,425 --> 00:25:43,944
A new vendor came in,
selling at a lower price.

264
00:25:43,945 --> 00:25:47,465
Same flavor and packaging as yours.

265
00:25:55,165 --> 00:25:56,165
Here, look.

266
00:25:57,785 --> 00:25:58,785
What?

267
00:26:05,065 --> 00:26:06,065
Hey.

268
00:26:07,805 --> 00:26:11,565
They even copied our logo.

269
00:26:12,785 --> 00:26:15,525
People these days,
shameless copycats.

270
00:26:16,345 --> 00:26:19,425
The only shop still carrying us
is Sun's friend's.

271
00:26:19,445 --> 00:26:20,505
Just one shop now.

272
00:26:25,545 --> 00:26:27,165
Why is this happening?

273
00:26:27,655 --> 00:26:30,085
Everything was starting
to come together.

274
00:26:30,665 --> 00:26:31,665
And now...

275
00:26:32,395 --> 00:26:35,705
with no money coming in,
how many months do we have left?

276
00:26:42,855 --> 00:26:43,565
Huh.

277
00:26:43,585 --> 00:26:45,465
With what we've got right now,

278
00:26:45,955 --> 00:26:48,355
probably two more months.

279
00:26:48,575 --> 00:26:49,905
What? Two months?

280
00:26:53,165 --> 00:26:57,225
Then, we'll need to notify
the children's guardians.

281
00:26:57,545 --> 00:27:00,505
If we have to close, they must
find somewhere else to go.

282
00:27:01,975 --> 00:27:03,365
We'll have to let them know.

283
00:27:05,445 --> 00:27:07,865
Where are we going to send them?

284
00:27:08,285 --> 00:27:10,305
We should start finding them
new places to stay.

285
00:27:21,785 --> 00:27:24,385
Aw... my plants just can't grow.

286
00:27:24,705 --> 00:27:25,784
You're not doing it right.

287
00:27:25,785 --> 00:27:28,765
- Haha.
- Haha.

288
00:27:28,795 --> 00:27:32,544
Look who's talking.
Yours are the most wilted of all.

289
00:27:32,545 --> 00:27:34,345
Yeah, look at yours.

290
00:27:37,185 --> 00:27:40,025
Guys, guys.

291
00:27:43,145 --> 00:27:44,905
This is bad. It's all bad.

292
00:27:44,935 --> 00:27:46,075
Yeah, it's all bad.

293
00:27:46,235 --> 00:27:49,025
Let's replant them,
or we'll have nothing to eat.

294
00:27:49,255 --> 00:27:51,705
Not the vegetables. It's us.

295
00:27:52,985 --> 00:27:56,065
I heard the adults talking.
This place is out of money.

296
00:27:56,125 --> 00:27:57,824
We must find a new place.

297
00:27:57,825 --> 00:27:59,025
- What?
- What?

298
00:28:40,675 --> 00:28:42,945
We must sell all of these.

299
00:28:45,165 --> 00:28:48,665
If we do, we won't have to
leave this house.

300
00:28:50,825 --> 00:28:53,425
You two are friends now?

301
00:28:56,265 --> 00:28:59,785
- We're calling a truce for now.
- We'll settle it later.

302
00:29:04,755 --> 00:29:08,025
Today is finally here.
The day we have to fight.

303
00:29:08,785 --> 00:29:11,065
Everyone here
is like a friend to me.

304
00:29:11,505 --> 00:29:13,145
Like a true family.

305
00:29:13,545 --> 00:29:15,385
I can't bear to watch you go.

306
00:29:16,455 --> 00:29:18,865
So we're gonna save Saeng Karun.

307
00:29:21,135 --> 00:29:22,135
Are you all in?

308
00:29:25,785 --> 00:29:27,145
- Fight.
- Let's do it.

309
00:29:27,315 --> 00:29:28,315
Ow.

310
00:29:28,765 --> 00:29:29,765
Ow.

311
00:29:30,385 --> 00:29:31,385
Ow.

312
00:29:32,285 --> 00:29:33,664
What's wrong, Pipe?

313
00:29:33,665 --> 00:29:36,665
My stomach... I've gone four times
to the restroom. Still hurts.

314
00:29:36,695 --> 00:29:39,575
Oh, dear.
You should've told me sooner.

315
00:29:39,595 --> 00:29:42,265
Let's get you
some electrolyte powder.

316
00:29:44,025 --> 00:29:44,645
Come, come.

317
00:29:44,665 --> 00:29:45,905
Ow.

318
00:29:47,945 --> 00:29:48,945
Ow.

319
00:29:50,545 --> 00:29:51,545
Ow.

320
00:30:03,765 --> 00:30:04,765
Ugh.

321
00:30:05,955 --> 00:30:07,455
The kids so quiet today, huh?

322
00:30:07,475 --> 00:30:08,905
Yeah, you're right.

323
00:30:09,395 --> 00:30:12,505
Usually, they raise a racket.

324
00:30:12,955 --> 00:30:15,785
If it were like this every day,
we'd have it so easy.

325
00:30:16,035 --> 00:30:17,035
That's true.

326
00:30:17,065 --> 00:30:18,065
Heh.

327
00:30:26,025 --> 00:30:27,025
I'll take this, yeah?

328
00:30:27,195 --> 00:30:29,905
Right, the kids
are probably waiting.

329
00:30:35,505 --> 00:30:36,585
Oh, Save.

330
00:30:37,255 --> 00:30:38,825
Has the email come back yet?

331
00:30:46,785 --> 00:30:49,425
Please let us have our channel back.

332
00:30:50,095 --> 00:30:51,705
Please let that happen.

333
00:30:53,865 --> 00:30:54,865
Huh.

334
00:31:01,355 --> 00:31:02,385
Snow.

335
00:31:06,785 --> 00:31:07,785
Pipe.

336
00:31:12,785 --> 00:31:13,785
Jedi.

337
00:31:28,345 --> 00:31:29,345
Snow.

338
00:31:34,525 --> 00:31:35,525
Pipe.

339
00:31:39,465 --> 00:31:40,465
Jedi.

340
00:31:46,285 --> 00:31:47,285
Snow.

341
00:31:54,865 --> 00:31:55,865
Deu.

342
00:31:56,505 --> 00:31:57,505
Jedi.

343
00:31:59,335 --> 00:32:00,335
Everyone.

344
00:32:13,515 --> 00:32:14,745
Mom, Mom.

345
00:32:14,905 --> 00:32:15,905
Hmm?

346
00:32:15,975 --> 00:32:17,885
Mom, Auntie Oui, the kids are gone.

347
00:32:17,905 --> 00:32:19,705
- What? How could that happen?
- What?

348
00:32:19,735 --> 00:32:21,345
I don't know.
They all just vanished.

349
00:32:21,365 --> 00:32:22,365
Hey.

350
00:32:22,445 --> 00:32:23,535
Come on.

351
00:32:23,705 --> 00:32:24,705
Oh, no.

352
00:32:31,065 --> 00:32:33,345
Hey, where did they go?

353
00:32:36,545 --> 00:32:37,545
Hey.

354
00:32:38,385 --> 00:32:39,745
Your snack bags, Mom.

355
00:32:40,165 --> 00:32:42,185
I thought you had put them away.

356
00:32:42,505 --> 00:32:44,785
I thought you had already
handed them out.

357
00:32:44,805 --> 00:32:45,805
Hmm?

358
00:32:45,815 --> 00:32:47,855
So where did they go with the bags?

359
00:32:48,445 --> 00:32:49,465
Oh.

360
00:32:53,545 --> 00:32:54,545
Yes.

361
00:32:55,785 --> 00:32:58,385
Yes, yes. Thank you so much.
We'll be right there.

362
00:32:59,665 --> 00:33:01,205
Khun On, our neighbor.

363
00:33:01,285 --> 00:33:03,745
She saw the kids
selling snacks at the market.

364
00:33:06,445 --> 00:33:07,705
Oh, that's Pipe.

365
00:33:08,095 --> 00:33:09,095
Hmm?

366
00:33:19,385 --> 00:33:22,665
Ah! He came to tell me
he had a stomachache.

367
00:33:22,705 --> 00:33:24,875
Probably stalling
so the others could slip out.

368
00:33:26,425 --> 00:33:28,025
Let's go to the market then.

369
00:33:29,075 --> 00:33:32,785
Wait, Oui, you stay.
In case they come back.

370
00:33:32,985 --> 00:33:33,915
Of course.

371
00:33:33,945 --> 00:33:35,785
- Let's go. What a headache.
- Go.

372
00:33:41,065 --> 00:33:42,995
Khun (honorific) On.

373
00:33:44,115 --> 00:33:45,264
Have you seen the kids?

374
00:33:45,265 --> 00:33:47,985
Over that way, and that way too.

375
00:33:48,265 --> 00:33:50,345
They've been hawking snacks.

376
00:33:50,805 --> 00:33:53,565
Go, go. Split up and find them.

377
00:33:53,775 --> 00:33:55,585
Okay, Save. Go with Grandpa.

378
00:33:56,545 --> 00:33:58,304
No, I can manage on my own.

379
00:33:58,305 --> 00:34:01,104
Dad, what if you fall?

380
00:34:01,105 --> 00:34:03,775
- Save, stay with him.
- Hurry, Phi Sorn.

381
00:34:06,155 --> 00:34:07,745
Let's go, Grandpa.

382
00:34:10,095 --> 00:34:11,095
Thank you.

383
00:34:13,745 --> 00:34:17,185
- Auntie Mart's Sanae Chan snacks.
- Sanae Chan snacks.

384
00:34:18,655 --> 00:34:20,825
- Want a box?
- Excuse me.

385
00:34:21,105 --> 00:34:22,824
Want some? They're really good.

386
00:34:22,825 --> 00:34:24,705
Auntie Mart's Sanae Chan snacks.

387
00:34:24,805 --> 00:34:25,984
No thanks, not interested.

388
00:34:25,985 --> 00:34:27,105
- Thank you.
- All right.

389
00:34:27,745 --> 00:34:29,825
Would you like a box?

390
00:34:30,225 --> 00:34:32,165
- Super delicious. Give them a try.
- No thank you.

391
00:34:32,185 --> 00:34:33,185
- Thank you.
- Thank you.

392
00:34:35,095 --> 00:34:38,365
Auntie, please support us. One box?

393
00:34:38,385 --> 00:34:39,944
- Want one?
- Just one box, Auntie.

394
00:34:39,945 --> 00:34:42,065
- Not for me.
- Please, Auntie.

395
00:34:42,085 --> 00:34:42,825
- Okay.
- Okay.

396
00:34:42,825 --> 00:34:43,825
No thanks.

397
00:34:46,025 --> 00:34:47,105
Excuse me.

398
00:34:48,005 --> 00:34:49,105
Want a box?

399
00:34:49,465 --> 00:34:50,905
No thanks.

400
00:35:02,255 --> 00:35:03,745
Not a single sale.

401
00:35:04,025 --> 00:35:05,545
- Same here.
- Same here.

402
00:35:07,105 --> 00:35:09,305
Hi, hi. Good-looking couple.

403
00:35:09,325 --> 00:35:11,285
Would you like some sweets?

404
00:35:11,305 --> 00:35:12,704
They're really good.

405
00:35:12,705 --> 00:35:15,265
It'll help us a lot.

406
00:35:15,285 --> 00:35:18,105
- So delicious.
- Please throw us a lifeline.

407
00:35:18,855 --> 00:35:20,064
It's like a dream.

408
00:35:20,065 --> 00:35:21,855
- Great price too.
- Please help.

409
00:35:21,885 --> 00:35:24,145
- Please, just one box.
- Take one with you.

410
00:35:24,165 --> 00:35:26,625
- So good, really.
- They're great.

411
00:35:27,565 --> 00:35:28,565
Huh.

412
00:35:29,785 --> 00:35:31,465
I'm tired. We've been at it all day.

413
00:35:31,525 --> 00:35:32,625
- Hmm.
- Nothing works.

414
00:35:33,175 --> 00:35:36,255
- We can't sell that way.
- True.

415
00:35:36,285 --> 00:35:37,285
What do we do?

416
00:35:39,025 --> 00:35:41,865
Mabel, Yoyo, Jingjai. You ready?

417
00:35:42,105 --> 00:35:43,225
- For what?
- Ready for what?

418
00:35:47,375 --> 00:35:51,575
Grandpa, you should sit down
and let me look for them.

419
00:35:52,185 --> 00:35:53,185
No.

420
00:35:55,385 --> 00:35:57,425
Woo-hoo...

421
00:35:58,865 --> 00:36:02,465
Woo... Woo.

422
00:36:06,585 --> 00:36:07,585
What's over there?

423
00:36:21,325 --> 00:36:23,545
- Woo...
- Woo...

424
00:36:25,005 --> 00:36:27,285
All right, kids.
I'll take three boxes.

425
00:36:27,325 --> 00:36:28,785
Hey, thanks.

426
00:36:31,805 --> 00:36:33,385
Here you go.

427
00:36:33,555 --> 00:36:34,985
140 baht. Wow.

428
00:36:35,085 --> 00:36:37,905
- Thank you.
- Thanks so much.

429
00:36:38,085 --> 00:36:39,765
Here, two boxes.

430
00:36:40,375 --> 00:36:42,145
Thank you very much.

431
00:36:42,445 --> 00:36:43,835
Thank you very much.

432
00:36:43,865 --> 00:36:45,305
Hey, we've just made 150 baht.

433
00:36:46,675 --> 00:36:48,625
These are so yummy.

434
00:36:48,945 --> 00:36:50,785
A taste you won't find
anywhere else.

435
00:36:51,065 --> 00:36:52,665
- Here you go.
- I'll try one.

436
00:36:53,325 --> 00:36:54,325
Go ahead.

437
00:37:00,705 --> 00:37:03,745
Hmm, soft on the tongue.
Good going down.

438
00:37:04,105 --> 00:37:05,745
How about the whole lot?

439
00:37:06,205 --> 00:37:09,745
- Yes.
- Yes.

440
00:37:11,705 --> 00:37:12,705
Thank you.

441
00:37:15,865 --> 00:37:18,305
Grandpa, Grandpa...

442
00:37:33,635 --> 00:37:36,825
We sold all of them.

443
00:37:38,065 --> 00:37:42,505
- Aren't we amazing?
- Our sweets got big thumbs up.

444
00:37:44,825 --> 00:37:45,825
Let's go home.

445
00:37:51,435 --> 00:37:54,265
Snow, you roped them all in, huh?

446
00:37:55,725 --> 00:37:56,725
Okay. Let's go home.

447
00:37:57,825 --> 00:37:58,825
Come.

448
00:38:04,115 --> 00:38:06,265
Shouldn't you
look after them better?

449
00:38:06,605 --> 00:38:08,385
Yeah, child labor.

450
00:38:23,765 --> 00:38:26,505
Who was behind all this?

451
00:38:36,605 --> 00:38:37,705
It was me.

452
00:38:38,295 --> 00:38:39,295
There you go.

453
00:38:40,195 --> 00:38:45,095
I just... did what I could
to keep my friends here.

454
00:38:45,565 --> 00:38:49,025
But you shouldn't have done that.
It's not safe out there.

455
00:38:50,935 --> 00:38:55,345
Go to your room until you've
thought about what you did.

456
00:38:58,985 --> 00:39:02,345
It wasn't just her.
I came up with the plan.

457
00:39:02,945 --> 00:39:08,105
- Me too.
- Me too.

458
00:39:22,835 --> 00:39:24,085
Please don't punish them.

459
00:39:25,285 --> 00:39:27,605
They just wanted to help.

460
00:39:28,345 --> 00:39:31,795
That's right, Director.
We love this place.

461
00:39:32,015 --> 00:39:33,775
We want to help.

462
00:39:34,495 --> 00:39:35,495
Right, everyone?

463
00:39:35,645 --> 00:39:37,305
- Right.
- Right.

464
00:39:40,245 --> 00:39:42,265
For your help,

465
00:39:44,585 --> 00:39:45,585
most admirable.

466
00:39:46,525 --> 00:39:49,865
I am deeply in your debt.

467
00:39:53,455 --> 00:39:55,325
We can help more, Grandpa.

468
00:39:55,945 --> 00:39:58,425
Just say it. Whatever it is.

469
00:39:58,745 --> 00:40:01,465
I'll hold you to that.

470
00:40:01,705 --> 00:40:06,345
But from now on,
no more sneaking out.

471
00:40:06,845 --> 00:40:09,985
Do not put yourself
in harm's way again.

472
00:40:10,575 --> 00:40:11,665
Understood?

473
00:40:11,975 --> 00:40:13,825
- Yes.
- Yes, Grandpa.

474
00:40:20,545 --> 00:40:22,185
Auntie Oui, why are you crying?

475
00:40:22,465 --> 00:40:24,105
I was worried sick
about all of you.

476
00:40:24,745 --> 00:40:28,065
You could've gotten hit
by a car out there.

477
00:40:28,085 --> 00:40:31,574
If someone went missing,
how would I live with myself?

478
00:40:31,575 --> 00:40:33,385
I've raised you all myself.

479
00:40:37,025 --> 00:40:39,345
I'm sorry for lying, Auntie Oui.

480
00:40:45,445 --> 00:40:49,945
Don't ever do that again.
I was so worried.

481
00:40:50,295 --> 00:40:51,905
- Yes.
- Yes.

482
00:41:41,325 --> 00:41:42,325
Grandpa.

483
00:41:44,395 --> 00:41:45,505
I want to apologize

484
00:41:47,205 --> 00:41:48,385
for saying those things.

485
00:41:50,145 --> 00:41:51,145
It's alright.

486
00:41:52,735 --> 00:41:54,705
I was the one who dropped the ball.

487
00:42:01,485 --> 00:42:02,485
Grandpa...

488
00:42:03,635 --> 00:42:04,675
shall we start over?

489
00:42:06,035 --> 00:42:08,725
All these years,
Saeng Karun has kept its doors open

490
00:42:09,095 --> 00:42:11,695
because of the money
from your great novels, right?

491
00:42:15,105 --> 00:42:16,785
You've done so much for this house.

492
00:42:20,395 --> 00:42:23,865
So? Any idea how to make money?

493
00:42:29,595 --> 00:42:31,705
Sitting around moping won't help.

494
00:42:32,665 --> 00:42:35,025
Do you have...
a life coach or someone

495
00:42:35,575 --> 00:42:36,575
who can help us?

496
00:42:37,425 --> 00:42:40,105
Life coach, what does that mean?

497
00:42:40,825 --> 00:42:44,625
Someone who helps lift our spirits
when we're running low.

498
00:42:45,385 --> 00:42:48,585
Or just someone we can lean on
when we need to.

499
00:42:48,965 --> 00:42:49,965
Anyone like that?

500
00:43:13,905 --> 00:43:15,985
Leaving your fate
in the Buddha's hands?

501
00:43:16,745 --> 00:43:18,545
Think he can sort it out for you?

502
00:43:19,225 --> 00:43:20,225
Why not?

503
00:43:20,905 --> 00:43:23,505
If it doesn't work, no harm done.

504
00:43:25,065 --> 00:43:28,465
But if it does, that's a bonus.
Right?

505
00:43:30,125 --> 00:43:31,865
Whatever appeases you.

506
00:43:45,035 --> 00:43:46,064
Done yet?

507
00:43:46,065 --> 00:43:47,065
Not yet.

508
00:44:01,295 --> 00:44:02,295
Who is it?

509
00:44:02,545 --> 00:44:04,665
An old friend, Nop.

510
00:44:05,505 --> 00:44:07,355
Oh, what now?

511
00:44:07,965 --> 00:44:10,555
When you're stressed,
you think of a friend?

512
00:44:11,935 --> 00:44:14,625
Aw, Grandma's going to
feel unwanted.

513
00:44:16,915 --> 00:44:19,825
A man doesn't tell his wife
when things get heavy.

514
00:44:20,185 --> 00:44:22,065
A wife can be someone
a man leans on.

515
00:44:22,615 --> 00:44:27,425
Your grandmother has always
been my strength all along.

516
00:44:27,565 --> 00:44:30,184
Aww...

517
00:44:30,185 --> 00:44:31,585
Sickeningly sweet.

518
00:44:33,945 --> 00:44:35,225
- Save.
- Hmm?

519
00:44:35,245 --> 00:44:38,025
Give me just a minute of quiet,
won't you?

520
00:44:39,605 --> 00:44:40,505
Fwee...

521
00:44:40,506 --> 00:44:42,265
Oh, okay, okay.

522
00:44:42,885 --> 00:44:43,885
Heh.

523
00:44:52,005 --> 00:44:53,005
Nop.

524
00:44:54,445 --> 00:44:56,425
We haven't talked in a while.

525
00:44:57,375 --> 00:45:00,305
You're lucky you went before me.

526
00:45:00,865 --> 00:45:03,345
But if you'd made it this far,

527
00:45:04,585 --> 00:45:06,985
you'd have just as much
of a headache as I do

528
00:45:07,805 --> 00:45:10,165
with all this nonsense
I keep running into.

529
00:45:12,475 --> 00:45:15,225
Everything's just
so different from our time.

530
00:45:33,785 --> 00:45:35,365
Hey, Nop.

531
00:45:36,185 --> 00:45:38,105
Hey, give that back.

532
00:45:38,135 --> 00:45:39,504
How do you write every day, Sak?

533
00:45:39,505 --> 00:45:40,505
Nop.

534
00:45:46,325 --> 00:45:47,325
Oh? A novel, is it?

535
00:45:57,315 --> 00:45:58,545
Hey, this is actually good.

536
00:46:00,265 --> 00:46:01,905
Ah-ha? Really?

537
00:46:02,145 --> 00:46:03,425
Yeah. Is there more?

538
00:46:03,945 --> 00:46:05,465
Just started it.
That's all there is.

539
00:46:06,625 --> 00:46:08,665
Finish it and send it
to a publisher.

540
00:46:08,985 --> 00:46:10,765
I'm telling you,
you could be a real writer.

541
00:46:16,785 --> 00:46:17,865
I'd love that.

542
00:46:19,105 --> 00:46:21,105
But I'm out of my depth with them.

543
00:46:25,095 --> 00:46:27,505
Who says? You're as good as them.

544
00:46:30,565 --> 00:46:33,985
You've got something
you can do anything with.

545
00:46:53,735 --> 00:46:57,545
Save, I'm sorry
for giving up so easily.

546
00:46:59,575 --> 00:47:02,705
It's okay, Grandpa.
It really is a challenge.

547
00:47:03,465 --> 00:47:04,585
I'm not upset anymore.

548
00:47:05,945 --> 00:47:08,024
I'm going back
to write the BL novel.

549
00:47:08,025 --> 00:47:09,025
What?

550
00:47:10,065 --> 00:47:12,065
No "what." You heard me.

551
00:47:12,265 --> 00:47:13,275
Are you serious?

552
00:47:13,665 --> 00:47:14,665
Dead serious.

553
00:47:14,845 --> 00:47:17,645
Why? Do I look like I'm joking?

554
00:47:28,105 --> 00:47:31,825
Please, let Guy not be
too angry with me.

555
00:47:34,065 --> 00:47:36,865
Leaving your fate
in the Buddha's hands?

556
00:47:37,385 --> 00:47:40,065
Think he can sort it out for you?

557
00:47:40,585 --> 00:47:43,985
Right now, this is what I can do.

558
00:47:45,065 --> 00:47:47,385
Sathu.

559
00:47:54,545 --> 00:47:56,785
"Guy, you there?"

560
00:48:05,425 --> 00:48:06,465
Pick up.

561
00:48:07,805 --> 00:48:10,665
Hey, give it back. Stop it.

562
00:48:11,025 --> 00:48:12,665
- Give it to me.
- It's mine.

563
00:48:12,695 --> 00:48:15,865
- Come on. Give me.
- It's mine.

564
00:48:16,265 --> 00:48:17,905
- Let me see.
- It's mine.

565
00:48:18,345 --> 00:48:19,705
- Hey, don't.
- Come on.

566
00:48:19,725 --> 00:48:21,345
- Hey, no.
- Let me play.

567
00:48:21,365 --> 00:48:23,104
- Stop pulling.
- I want to play.

568
00:48:23,105 --> 00:48:24,975
- Pipe, Pipe.
- What is this?

569
00:48:26,145 --> 00:48:27,184
New toy?

570
00:48:27,185 --> 00:48:28,185
Yes.

571
00:48:28,665 --> 00:48:29,665
Where'd you get it?

572
00:48:29,666 --> 00:48:30,905
Phi Guy gave it to me.

573
00:48:45,335 --> 00:48:47,305
Oh, hi, Phi Guy.

574
00:48:47,825 --> 00:48:48,825
Mm-hmm.

575
00:48:51,995 --> 00:48:53,065
Here, take it.

576
00:48:53,345 --> 00:48:55,945
Wow, it looks expensive.

577
00:48:56,285 --> 00:48:57,615
Are you sure?

578
00:48:58,415 --> 00:48:59,415
Yeah.

579
00:49:00,355 --> 00:49:01,625
You won't want it back?

580
00:49:02,025 --> 00:49:03,025
Want it or not?

581
00:49:03,155 --> 00:49:05,765
Of course. Thanks, Phi Guy.

582
00:49:20,505 --> 00:49:22,385
He is so kind.

583
00:49:22,705 --> 00:49:25,465
But he hasn't come around anymore.

584
00:49:25,695 --> 00:49:29,865
Can you tell him to visit us?
I want to play soccer with him.

585
00:49:32,865 --> 00:49:33,984
And I'm vanishing.

586
00:49:33,985 --> 00:49:35,905
Hey, wait. Pipe.

587
00:49:39,665 --> 00:49:40,665
"Sorry."

588
00:49:40,805 --> 00:49:44,024
"The number you have dialed
is not available at this time."

589
00:49:44,025 --> 00:49:45,185
He turned the phone off?

590
00:50:03,985 --> 00:50:04,985
Grandpa.

591
00:50:07,085 --> 00:50:08,545
Without Save and Guy,

592
00:50:09,325 --> 00:50:10,705
can you write the novel?

593
00:50:11,505 --> 00:50:14,065
Your input has helped a lot.

594
00:50:15,505 --> 00:50:17,895
But if you and your friend
are in a tough spot,

595
00:50:18,075 --> 00:50:19,665
I can find another way.

596
00:50:34,885 --> 00:50:36,265
Thanks, Nop.

597
00:51:11,405 --> 00:51:12,965
"1"

598
00:51:14,365 --> 00:51:16,225
Guy is my best friend.

599
00:51:17,745 --> 00:51:19,945
An old friend, Nop.

600
00:51:25,625 --> 00:51:28,465
Hey, Nop. The publisher wrote back.

601
00:51:29,155 --> 00:51:30,225
Read it to me.

602
00:51:38,235 --> 00:51:39,235
Sak.

603
00:51:40,065 --> 00:51:42,705
Congrats.
They're gonna publish your novel.

604
00:51:45,185 --> 00:51:47,745
Aren't you happy?
You're gonna a real writer.

605
00:51:48,475 --> 00:51:50,145
Your dream is coming true.

606
00:51:51,995 --> 00:51:53,065
Hey, it got accepted.

607
00:51:57,905 --> 00:51:58,905
Let me see.

608
00:52:02,305 --> 00:52:04,465
Prasit, see?
Somsak Prasit.

609
00:52:04,855 --> 00:52:06,975
We are pleased to welcome you
as our writer.

610
00:52:19,615 --> 00:52:25,545
"Tall dense trees lined every step
of the rugged jungle path."

611
00:52:25,945 --> 00:52:30,985
"Tender leaves swayed
and caught the last light of dusk."

612
00:52:31,545 --> 00:52:37,865
"Two men walked side by side,
deeper into the woods."

613
00:52:52,635 --> 00:52:57,505
"Their faces slick with sweat
and smeared with mud."

614
00:52:59,025 --> 00:53:00,825
"Breath ragged and heavy."

615
00:53:01,905 --> 00:53:07,945
"Yet the strength between them
moved in perfect sync."

616
00:53:09,425 --> 00:53:15,185
"In their eyes, a bond reflected"

617
00:53:15,745 --> 00:53:18,225
"too deep for anyone else
to understand."

618
00:53:25,105 --> 00:53:26,705
You patched things up with him yet?

619
00:53:27,625 --> 00:53:28,625
Guy.

620
00:53:28,905 --> 00:53:31,425
Sounds like he's cut you
out of his life.

621
00:53:31,705 --> 00:53:34,664
Maybe it's time to
try a little harder.

622
00:53:34,665 --> 00:53:35,785
What do I do, Grandpa?

623
00:53:36,455 --> 00:53:37,625
Make him something.

624
00:53:38,225 --> 00:53:39,225
I don't want it.

625
00:53:39,945 --> 00:53:43,025
You told me yourself that things
can't go back to how they were.

626
00:53:44,945 --> 00:53:50,824
The world keeps
turning every day.

627
00:53:50,825 --> 00:53:56,144
And we keep turning in its play.

628
00:53:56,145 --> 00:53:59,385
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

629
00:53:59,565 --> 00:54:02,104
We just might see
the world within.

630
00:54:02,105 --> 00:54:06,144
Let's walk together, day by day.

631
00:54:06,145 --> 00:54:11,145
Come take the step,
what do you say?

632
00:54:17,685 --> 00:54:21,304
Let us be real,
not dreaming away,

633
00:54:21,305 --> 00:54:25,224
We'll walk in the light
of a new day.

634
00:54:25,225 --> 00:54:30,264
No one can tell
what tomorrow may say.

635
00:54:30,265 --> 00:54:32,744
Wherever the gentle wind blows,

636
00:54:32,745 --> 00:54:35,544
let our hearts flow,
soft and slow.

637
00:54:35,545 --> 00:54:40,345
And land where
our hearts both grow.

638
00:54:40,705 --> 00:54:46,624
The world keeps
turning every day.

639
00:54:46,625 --> 00:54:51,864
And we keep turning in its play.

640
00:54:51,865 --> 00:54:55,065
Just open up, we'll learn it in.

641
00:54:55,425 --> 00:54:57,904
We just might see
the world within.

642
00:54:57,905 --> 00:55:01,984
Let's walk together, day by day.

643
00:55:01,985 --> 00:55:06,865
Come take the step,
what do you say?

